–Ø –ø–æ–¥–≥–æ—Ç–æ–≤–ª—é –ø–æ–ª–Ω–æ–µ –¢–ó, –æ—Ä–≥–∞–Ω–∏–∑—É—è –∏–Ω—Ñ–æ—Ä–º–∞—Ü–∏—é –ø–æ –ª–æ–≥–∏—á–µ—Å–∫–∏–º –±–ª–æ–∫–∞–º, –∫–∞–∫ –º—ã –æ–±—Å—É–∂–¥–∞–ª–∏ –≤ –¥–∏–∞–ª–æ–≥–µ","phase":"think","status":"finished","extra":null,"role":"assistant","usage":{"input_tokens":168010,"output_tokens":378,"total_tokens":168388,"output_tokens_details":{"reasoning_tokens":370}}},{"content":"# üéª TECHNICAL SPECIFICATION: MUSIC CONNECTIONS PWA\n# Interactive Encyclopedia of Musical Connections\n# Version 3.0 with Full Context Automation System\n# Generated: 2024-11-04 16:45:23 UTC\n# Author: apel-s-in\n# Repository: https://github.com/apel-s-in/music-connections\n\n#===============================================================================\n# PROJECT OVERVIEW AND GOALS\n#===============================================================================\n\n## MISSION STATEMENT\nCreate an interactive visual encyclopedia showing connections between violinists, their teachers, instrument makers, and historical events through an intuitive interface adapted for children and researchers.\n\n## CORE PRINCIPLES\n- Zero-backend architecture: All data stored in JSON/YAML files in repository\n- Mobile-first design: Full adaptation for all devices and screen orientations\n- Vector graphics: SVG shapes instead of raster images for scalability\n- Security first: Multi-level protection for admin panel and data\n- Open source: MIT license with full transparency\n- Accessibility: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance for users with disabilities\n\n## TARGET AUDIENCES\n| Group | Needs | Interface Features |\n|-------|-------|-------------------|\n| Children 8-14 | Gamified approach, animations, simplicity | Bright colors, large buttons, sound effects |\n| Musicians | Data accuracy, export capabilities | Detailed biographies, PDF export, analytics |\n| Researchers | Historical precision | Calendar support (Julian/Gregorian), sources |\n| Teachers | Educational content | Ready lesson scenarios, filters |\n\n#===============================================================================\n# TECHNOLOGICAL STACK\n#===============================================================================\n\n## CORE TECHNOLOGIES\n| Category | Technology | Version | Justification |\n|----------|------------|---------|--------------|\n| Framework | Next.js | 14.2.3 | App Router, PWA support, Server Components |\n| Language | TypeScript | 5.4 | Static typing for complex logic |\n| Styling | Tailwind CSS + CSS-in-JS | 3.4 | Responsive design without media queries |\n| Visualization | D3.js + React Flow | 7.8 | Flexible graphs and timelines |\n| Vector Graphics | SVG + Framer Motion | 11.1 | Animations without raster images |\n| PWA | next-pwa + Workbox | 5.6 | Offline access, installation |\n| AI | Yandex GPT API | v1 | Data analysis and recommendations |\n| Hosting | Vercel + Cloudflare | - | Free hosting with protection |\n\n## ADDITIONAL LIBRARIES\n```json\n{\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@yandex-cloud/nodejs-sdk\": \"^1.1.0\",\n    \"d3\": \"^7.8.5\",\n    \"date-fns\": \"^3.3.1\",\n    \"fuse.js\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"jsonwebtoken\": \"^9.0.2\",\n    \"next-pwa\": \"^5.6.0\",\n    \"pdf-lib\": \"^1.17.1\",\n    \"react-flow-renderer\": \"^11.10.1\",\n    \"react-icons\": \"^5.0.1\",\n    \"yup\": \"^1.3.3\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\": \"^20.11.25\",\n    \"@types/react\": \"^18.2.64\",\n    \"@types/react-dom\": \"^18.2.21\",\n    \"autoprefixer\": \"^10.4.18\",\n    \"postcss\": \"^8.4.35\",\n    \"tailwindcss\": \"^3.4.1\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#===============================================================================\n# PROJECT STRUCTURE\n#===============================================================================\n\n```\n/music-connections\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .meta/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ project-full.txt          # Complete project context (unlimited)\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ project-adaptive.txt      # Adaptive context (10,000 lines max)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .github/workflows\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ build.yml                 # Build and deployment\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ backup-to-yandex.yml      # Backup to Yandex.Disk\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ security-audit.yml        # Security checks\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ data\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ people\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ heifetz.yaml          # Jascha Heifetz (1901-1987)\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ paganini.yaml         # Nicolo Paganini (1782-1840)\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ... (10 initial people)\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ events\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ carnegie-1917.yaml    # Carnegie Hall debut (1917)\n‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ... (25 initial events)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ lib\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ai-analysis.ts            # Yandex GPT integration\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ backup-utils.ts           # Yandex.Disk backup utilities\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ date-utils.ts             # Calendar support (Julian/Gregorian)\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pdf-export.ts             # PDF export functionality\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ security.ts               # Security functions\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ telegram.ts               # Telegram bot integration\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ public\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ icons\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ violin.svg            # Violin icon\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ cello.svg             # Cello icon\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ... \n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ manifest.json             # PWA manifest\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ scripts\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ build-connections.js      # Automatic connections builder\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ generate-context.js       # Context files generator\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ restore-from-yandex.sh    # Backup restoration script\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ app\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ (main)\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ layout.tsx        # Main layout\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ page.tsx          # Main page\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ timeline\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ page.tsx      # Timeline page\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ admin\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ layout.tsx        # Protected admin layout\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ dashboard.tsx     # Admin dashboard\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ai-recommendations.tsx # AI recommendations\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ api\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ auth\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ route.ts      # GitHub OAuth\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ backup\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ route.ts      # Backup to Yandex.Disk\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ai-analysis\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ route.ts      # Yandex GPT analysis\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ feedback\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ route.ts          # Feedback route\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ui\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ VectorIcons.tsx   # Vector icons\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ResponsiveContainer.tsx # Responsive containers\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ShapeComponents.tsx # SVG shapes\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ timeline\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ TimelineScale.tsx\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ EventNode.tsx\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ graph\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ConnectionGraph.tsx\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ NodeComponent.tsx\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ admin\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ AIRecommendationsPanel.tsx\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ DataEditor.tsx\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ styles\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ globals.css\n‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ animations.css\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .env.example\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ next.config.js\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ postcss.config.js\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ tailwind.config.js\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ package.json\n```\n\n#===============================================================================\n# KEY FUNCTIONALITY\n#===============================================================================\n\n## 1. ADAPTIVE TIMELINE\n- Horizontal line with 1 day scale division\n- Dynamic zoom: from centuries to days\n- Random people: 5 violinists at initial position\n- Responsive design: different layouts for portrait/landscape modes\n- Zoom functionality: pinch-to-zoom and scroll wheel support\n- Event highlighting: connections to selected person appear semi-transparently\n\n### Technical Implementation\n```typescript\n// components/timeline/Timeline.tsx\n'use client';\n\nimport { useRef, useEffect, useState } from 'react';\nimport * as d3 from 'd3';\nimport { VectorIcon } from '../ui/VectorIcons';\nimport { EventShape } from '../ui/ShapeComponents';\n\nexport default function Timeline() {\n  const svgRef = useRef<SVGSVGElement>(null);\n  const containerRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);\n  const [viewBox, setViewBox] = useState({ x: 0, y: 0, width: 800, height: 150 });\n  const [isDragging, setIsDragging] = useState(false);\n  \n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!svgRef.current || !containerRef.current) return;\n    \n    const svg = d3.select(svgRef.current);\n    const container = containerRef.current;\n    const width = container.clientWidth;\n    const height = 150;\n    \n    // Initial scale boundaries\n    const startDate = new Date(1600, 0, 1); // Start from Stradivari\n    const endDate = new Date(); // Today\n    \n    // Time scale\n    const xScale = d3.scaleTime()\n      .domain([startDate, endDate])\n      .range([50, width - 50]);\n    \n    // Line for timeline\n    svg.append('line')\n      .attr('x1', 50)\n      .attr('y1', height / 2)\n      .attr('x2', width - 50)\n      .attr('y2', height / 2)\n      .attr('stroke', '#9ca3af')\n      .attr('stroke-width', 2);\n    \n    // Year markers\n    const ticks = xScale.ticks(d3.timeYear.every(10));\n    ticks.forEach((date, i) => {\n      const x = xScale(date);\n      \n      // Tick line\n      svg.append('line')\n        .attr('x1', x)\n        .attr('y1', height / 2 - 5)\n        .attr('x2', x)\n        .attr('y2', height / 2 + 5)\n        .attr('stroke', '#6b7280')\n        .attr('stroke-width', 1);\n      \n      // Year label\n      svg.append('text')\n        .attr('x', x)\n        .attr('y', height / 2 + 20)\n        .attr('text-anchor', 'middle')\n        .attr('font-size', '10px')\n        .attr('fill', '#6b7280')\n        .text(date.getFullYear());\n    });\n    \n    // Setup drag and zoom handlers...\n  }, []);\n  \n  return (\n    <div \n      ref={containerRef} \n      className=\"w-full bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 shadow-sm relative overflow-hidden\"\n      style={{ cursor: isDragging ? 'grabbing' : 'grab' }}\n    >\n      <svg\n        ref={svgRef}\n        viewBox={`${viewBox.x} ${viewBox.y} ${viewBox.width} ${viewBox.height}`}\n        className=\"w-full h-48 transition-transform duration-100\"\n      >\n        {/* Elements will be added via D3 */}\n      </svg>\n      \n      {/* Control buttons */}\n      <div className=\"absolute top-2 right-2 flex space-x-2\">\n        <button \n          onClick={() => setViewBox(prev => ({ ...prev, width: prev.width * 0.9 }))}\n          className=\"p-1 bg-gray-100 rounded-full hover:bg-gray-200\"\n          title=\"Zoom in\"\n        >\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" strokeWidth=\"2\">\n            <circle cx=\"11\" cy=\"11\" r=\"8\" />\n            <line x1=\"21\" y1=\"21\" x2=\"16.65\" y2=\"16.65\" />\n            <line x1=\"11\" y1=\"8\" x2=\"11\" y2=\"14\" />\n            <line x1=\"8\" y1=\"11\" x2=\"14\" y2=\"11\" />\n          </svg>\n        </button>\n        <button \n          onClick={() => setViewBox(prev => ({ ...prev, width: prev.width * 1.1 }))}\n          className=\"p-1 bg-gray-100 rounded-full hover:bg-gray-200\"\n          title=\"Zoom out\"\n        >\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" strokeWidth=\"2\">\n            <circle cx=\"11\" cy=\"11\" r=\"8\" />\n            <line x1=\"21\" y1=\"21\" x2=\"16.65\" y2=\"16.65\" />\n            <line x1=\"11\" y1=\"8\" x2=\"11\" y2=\"14\" />\n          </svg>\n        </button>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n## 2. CONNECTION SYSTEM AND HIGHLIGHTING\n- Color coding system:\n  | Connection Type | Color | Symbol | Icon |\n  |-----------------|-------|--------|------|\n  | Teacher/student | #2563eb | üë®‚Äçüè´ | FaUserGraduate |\n  | Concert | #8b5cf6 | üéª | FaUsers |\n  | Relative | #ef4444 | ‚ù§Ô∏è | FaHeart |\n  | Instrument maker | #16a34a | ü™µ | FaTools |\n  | Friendship | #f59e0b | ü§ù | FaHandshake |\n\n### Technical Implementation\n```typescript\n// components/graph/ConnectionGraph.tsx\nimport { VectorIcon } from '../ui/VectorIcons';\nimport { ConnectionLine } from '../ui/ShapeComponents';\n\nconst CONNECTION_STYLES = {\n  teacher: { color: '#2563eb', icon: 'FaUserGraduate' },\n  concert: { color: '#8b5cf6', icon: 'FaUsers' },\n  relative: { color: '#ef4444', icon: 'FaHeart' },\n  instrument: { color: '#16a34a', icon: 'FaTools' },\n  friend: { color: '#f59e0b', icon: 'FaHandshake' }\n};\n\nexport function ConnectionGraph({ data, selectedNodeId }: {  any; selectedNodeId: string | null }) {\n  const [highlightedNodes, setHighlightedNodes] = useState<string[]>([]);\n  \n  const handleNodeClick = (nodeId: string) => {\n    setSelectedNode(nodeId);\n    \n    // Find related nodes\n    const relatedNodes = data.connections\n      .filter(conn => conn.source === nodeId || conn.target === nodeId)\n      .map(conn => conn.source === nodeId ? conn.target : conn.source);\n      \n    setHighlightedNodes([...relatedNodes, nodeId]);\n  };\n  \n  return (\n    <div className=\"relative w-full h-[600px] bg-gray-50\">\n      {data.connections.map((conn: any) => (\n        <ConnectionLine\n          key={`${conn.source}-${conn.target}`}\n          start={{ x: getNodeX(conn.source), y: getNodeY(conn.source) }}\n          end={{ x: getNodeX(conn.target), y: getNodeY(conn.target) }}\n          type={conn.type}\n          highlighted={highlightedNodes.includes(conn.source) || highlightedNodes.includes(conn.target)}\n        />\n      ))}\n      \n      {data.people.map((person: any) => (\n        <div \n          key={person.id}\n          className={`absolute transform -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 cursor-pointer transition-all duration-300 ${\n            highlightedNodes.includes(person.id) \n              ? 'scale-125 z-10' \n              : 'scale-100 z-0'\n          }`}\n          style={{ \n            left: `${getNodeX(person.id)}px`, \n            top: `${getNodeY(person.id)}px` \n          }}\n          onClick={() => handleNodeClick(person.id)}\n        >\n          <div className={`w-12 h-12 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center ${\n            selectedNodeId === person.id \n              ? 'bg-blue-500 text-white shadow-lg' \n              : 'bg-white shadow-md'\n          }`}>\n            <VectorIcon type=\"violinist\" size={24} className=\"text-blue-600\" />\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"mt-1 text-xs text-center font-medium\">{person.names.primary}</div>\n        </div>\n      ))}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n## 3. ADMIN PANEL WITH YANDEX GPT INTEGRATION\n- Authentication via GitHub OAuth\n- AI recommendations panel with automatic suggestions\n- Data editor with validation\n- Security audit logs\n- Context-aware code generation instructions\n\n### Technical Implementation\n```typescript\n// app/api/ai-analysis/route.ts\nimport { NextResponse } from 'next/server';\nimport { withAdminProtection } from '@/lib/security';\nimport { getAIRecommendations } from '@/lib/ai-analysis';\n\nexport const POST = withAdminProtection(async (req: Request, res: NextResponse, user: any) => {\n  try {\n    const { data } = await req.json();\n    \n    // Rate limiting\n    const rateLimitKey = `ai_requests:${user.githubId}:${Math.floor(Date.now() / 60000)}`;\n    const currentRequests = await getRateLimitCount(rateLimitKey);\n    \n    if (currentRequests >= 10) { // 10 requests per minute\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { error: 'Too many requests', retry_after: 60 - (Date.now() % 60000) / 1000 }, \n        { status: 429 }\n      );\n    }\n    \n    await incrementRateLimit(rateLimitKey);\n    \n    // Get AI recommendations\n    const recommendations = await getAIRecommendations(data);\n    \n    // Log activity\n    logActivity('ai_analysis', { \n      userId: user.githubId, \n      itemsAnalyzed: data.people.length, \n      recommendations: recommendations.new_events.length \n    });\n    \n    return NextResponse.json(recommendations);\n    \n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('AI API Error:', error);\n    logError('ai_analysis', error);\n    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'AI analysis failed' }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n});\n```\n\n## 4. TELEGRAM FEEDBACK SYSTEM\n- Two-way communication with users\n- Email confirmation option\n- Message logging\n- Response tracking\n\n### Technical Implementation\n```typescript\n// lib/telegram.ts\nexport async function sendTelegramMessage(text: string) {\n  const botToken = process.env.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN!;\n  const chatId = process.env.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID!;\n  \n  const response = await fetch(\n    `https://api.telegram.org/bot${botToken}/sendMessage`,\n    {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ \n        chat_id: chatId, \n        text, \n        parse_mode: 'HTML',\n        disable_web_page_preview: true\n      }),\n    }\n  );\n  \n  if (!response.ok) {\n    const errorData = await response.json();\n    throw new Error(`Telegram API error: ${errorData.description}`);\n  }\n  \n  return response.json();\n}\n\n// app/api/feedback/route.ts\nexport async function POST(request: NextRequest) {\n  try {\n    const { name, email, message, contactMethod } = await request.json();\n    \n    // Validation\n    if (!name || !message) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { error: 'Name and message are required' }, \n        { status: 400 }\n      );\n    }\n    \n    // Send to Telegram\n    const telegramMessage = `\nüîî New feedback message\n      \nüë§ Name: ${name}\nüìß Email: ${email || 'not provided'}\nüì± Contact method: ${contactMethod || 'not specified'}\n      \nüí¨ Message:\n${message}\n    `;\n    \n    await sendTelegramMessage(telegramMessage);\n    \n    // Send confirmation if requested\n    if (contactMethod === 'email' && email) {\n      await sendEmailConfirmation(email, name, message);\n    } else if (contactMethod === 'telegram') {\n      await sendTelegramConfirmation(name);\n    }\n    \n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true });\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('Feedback error:', error);\n    return NextResponse.json(\n      { error: 'Failed to send message' }, \n      { status: 500 }\n    );\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## 5. PDF EXPORT FUNCTIONALITY\n- Export life lines as professional PDF\n- Custom styling and branding\n- Proper pagination and headers\n- Multi-language support\n\n### Technical Implementation\n```typescript\n// lib/pdf-export.ts\nimport { PDFDocument, StandardFonts, rgb } from 'pdf-lib';\nimport fontkit from '@pdf-lib/fontkit';\n\nexport async function exportLifeLinesToPDF(people: any[], events: any[]) {\n  const pdfDoc = await PDFDocument.create();\n  pdfDoc.registerFontkit(fontkit);\n  \n  // Add font\n  const fontBytes = await fetch('/fonts/Roboto-Regular.ttf').then(res => res.arrayBuffer());\n  const customFont = await pdfDoc.embedFont(fontBytes);\n  \n  const page = pdfDoc.addPage();\n  const { width, height } = page.getSize();\n  \n  // Header\n  page.drawText('Life Paths of Violinists', {\n    x: 50,\n    y: height - 50,\n    size: 24,\n    font: customFont,\n    color: rgb(0.1, 0.1, 0.1),\n  });\n  \n  // Page content\n  let yPos = height - 100;\n  for (const person of people) {\n    // Person name and lifespan\n    page.drawText(`${person.names.primary} (${person.birth.display} - ${person.death?.display || 'present'})`, {\n      x: 50,\n      y: yPos,\n      size: 16,\n      font: customFont,\n      color: rgb(0.2, 0.4, 0.8),\n    });\n    \n    yPos -= 25;\n    \n    // Events\n    for (const eventId of person.events) {\n      const event = events.find(e => e.id === eventId);\n      if (event) {\n        page.drawText(`‚Ä¢ ${event.date.display}: ${event.title.primary}`, {\n          x: 70,\n          y: yPos,\n          size: 12,\n          font: customFont,\n          color: rgb(0.3, 0.3, 0.3),\n        });\n        yPos -= 20;\n      }\n    }\n    \n    yPos -= 10;\n    \n    // Break to new page if needed\n    if (yPos < 100) {\n      page.drawText('Page ' + pdfDoc.getPages().length, {\n        x: width - 60,\n        y: 30,\n        size: 10,\n        font: customFont,\n        color: rgb(0.6, 0.6, 0.6),\n      });\n      \n      page = pdfDoc.addPage();\n      yPos = height - 70;\n    }\n  }\n  \n  // Footer on last page\n  page.drawText(`Exported: ${new Date().toLocaleDateString()}`, {\n    x: 50,\n    y: 30,\n    size: 10,\n    font: customFont,\n    color: rgb(0.6, 0.6, 0.6),\n  });\n  page.drawText(`Page ${pdfDoc.getPages().length}`, {\n    x: width - 60,\n    y: 30,\n    size: 10,\n    font: customFont,\n    color: rgb(0.6, 0.6, 0.6),\n  });\n  \n  return await pdfDoc.save();\n}\n```\n\n## 6. YANDEX.DONATE INTEGRATION\n- Floating donation button\n- Multiple amount options\n- Analytics tracking\n- Mobile-friendly design\n\n### Technical Implementation\n```tsx\n// components/DonationButton.tsx\n'use client';\n\nimport { useState } from 'react';\n\nexport default function DonationButton() {\n  const [donationAmount, setDonationAmount] = useState(300);\n  const [isProcessing, setIsProcessing] = useState(false);\n  \n  const handleDonate = () => {\n    if (isProcessing) return;\n    \n    setIsProcessing(true);\n    \n    // Yandex.Donate URL\n    const donationUrl = `https://yoomoney.ru/quickpay/shop-widget?writer=seller&targets=Support+for+Music+Connections+Project&targets-hint=&default-sum=${donationAmount}&button-text=01&hint=&successURL=&quickpay=shop&account=410011234567890&currency=1&paymentType=AC`;\n    \n    // Open in new window\n    window.open(donationUrl, '_blank');\n    \n    // Analytics\n    if (window.plausible) {\n      window.plausible('DonationStarted', { props: { amount: donationAmount } });\n    }\n    \n    setIsProcessing(false);\n  };\n  \n  return (\n    <div className=\"fixed bottom-4 right-4 z-50\">\n      <div className=\"bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-4 border border-gray-200 max-w-xs\">\n        <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between mb-3\">\n          <div className=\"flex items-center space-x-2\">\n            <div className=\"bg-yellow-100 p-2 rounded-full\">\n              <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" strokeWidth=\"2\">\n                <path strokeLinecap=\"round\" strokeLinejoin=\"round\" d=\"M12 6v6m0 0v6m0-6h6m-6 0H6\" />\n              </svg>\n            </div>\n            <div>\n              <div className=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Support the Project</div>\n              <div className=\"text-sm text-gray-500\">Your help is important for development</div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n          <button \n            onClick={() => setDonationAmount(donationAmount === 300 ? 500 : 300)}\n            className=\"text-sm font-medium text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800\"\n          >\n            {donationAmount === 300 ? '500 ‚ÇΩ' : '300 ‚ÇΩ'}\n          </button>\n        </div>\n        \n        <button\n          onClick={handleDonate}\n          disabled={isProcessing}\n          className={`w-full py-3 px-4 rounded-lg font-medium text-white transition-colors ${\n            isProcessing \n              ? 'bg-gray-400 cursor-not-allowed' \n              : 'bg-gradient-to-r from-yellow-400 to-yellow-600 hover:from-yellow-500 hover:to-yellow-700'\n          }`}\n        >\n          {isProcessing ? (\n            <div className=\"flex items-center justify-center\">\n              <div className=\"animate-spin rounded-full h-4 w-4 border-b-2 border-white mr-2\"></div>\n              Processing...\n            </div>\n          ) : (\n            `Support with ${donationAmount} ‚ÇΩ`\n          )}\n        </button>\n        \n        <div className=\"mt-3 text-xs text-gray-500 text-center\">\n          All funds will go to project development and server costs\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n## 7. BACKUP TO YANDEX.DISK\n- Automatic daily backups\n- Encrypted archives\n- Retention policy (7 days)\n- Failure notifications\n- Manual restore capability\n\n### GitHub Actions Workflow\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/backup-to-yandex.yml\nname: Backup to Yandex Disk\n\non:\n  schedule:\n    - cron: '0 3 * * *'  # Daily at 3:00 UTC\n  workflow_dispatch:\n\njobs:\n  backup:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    env:\n      YANDEX_DISK_USERNAME: ${{ secrets.YANDEX_DISK_USERNAME }}\n      YANDEX_DISK_APP_PASSWORD: ${{ secrets.YANDEX_DISK_APP_PASSWORD }}\n      \n    steps:\n      - name: Checkout repository\n        uses: actions/checkout@v4\n        \n      - name: Create backup archive\n        run: |\n          TIMESTAMP=$(date -u +\"%Y%m%d_%H%M%S\")\n          BACKUP_FILE=\"music-connections-backup-${TIMESTAMP}.tar.gz\"\n          \n          tar -czf $BACKUP_FILE \\\n            --exclude='.git' \\\n            --exclude='node_modules' \\\n            --exclude='*.env*' \\\n            --exclude='logs' \\\n            data/ \\\n            scripts/ \\\n            package.json \\\n            .github/workflows/\n          \n          echo \"BACKUP_FILE=$BACKUP_FILE\" >> $GITHUB_ENV\n          echo \"Backup created: $BACKUP_FILE ($(du -h $BACKUP_FILE | cut -f1))\"\n      \n      - name: Encrypt backup\n        run: |\n          # Generate random password\n          ARCHIVE_PASSWORD=$(openssl rand -base64 32)\n          echo \"ARCHIVE_PASSWORD=$ARCHIVE_PASSWORD\" >> $GITHUB_ENV\n          \n          # Encrypt archive\n          7z a -t7z -mhe=on -p\"$ARCHIVE_PASSWORD\" \"${{ env.BACKUP_FILE }}.7z\" \"${{ env.BACKUP_FILE }}\"\n          \n          # Save password securely\n          echo \"$ARCHIVE_PASSWORD\" | gpg --encrypt --recipient YOUR_GPG_KEY_ID -o password.gpg\n          \n          # Remove original file\n          rm \"${{ env.BACKUP_FILE }}\"\n      \n      - name: Upload to Yandex.Disk\n        run: |\n          # Install cadaver for WebDAV\n          sudo apt-get update\n          sudo apt-get install -y cadaver curl jq\n      \n          # Upload encrypted file\n          cadaver -t https://webdav.yandex.ru << EOF\n          cd /music-connections-backups\n          put ${{ env.BACKUP_FILE }}.7z\n          put password.gpg\n          ls -la\n          quit\n          EOF\n          \n          if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then\n            echo \"::error::Upload failed\"\n            exit 1\n          fi\n          \n          echo \"‚úÖ Backup uploaded successfully\"\n      \n      - name: Cleanup\n        if: always()\n        run: |\n          rm -f ${{ env.BACKUP_FILE }}.7z password.gpg\n```\n\n## 8. CONTEXT GENERATION SYSTEM\n- Automatic generation of project context files\n- Two versions: full (unlimited) and adaptive (10,000 lines)\n- Priority-based content inclusion\n- Proper indentation preservation\n- Integration with GitHub Actions\n\n### Context Generation Script\n```javascript\n// scripts/generate-context.js\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\n\nconst PROJECT_ROOT = path.join(__dirname, '..');\nconst META_DIR = path.join(PROJECT_ROOT, '.meta');\nconst FULL_FILE = path.join(META_DIR, 'project-full.txt');\nconst ADAPTIVE_FILE = path.join(META_DIR, 'project-adaptive.txt');\n\n// Configuration\nconst CONFIG = {\n  scanExclude: [\n    'node_modules/**',\n    '.git/**',\n    '.next/**',\n    'logs/**',\n    'dist/**',\n    'coverage/**',\n    '.DS_Store',\n    '.env',\n    '.env.local',\n    'package-lock.json',\n    '.eslintcache',\n    '.prettiercache',\n    '.idea/**',\n    '.vscode/**',\n    '*.log',\n    '*.tmp',\n    '*.swp',\n    '*.swo',\n    'yarn.lock',\n    'pnpm-lock.yaml',\n    '.meta/project-full.txt',\n    '.meta/project-adaptive.txt'\n  ],\n  \n  fullContentTypes: [\n    '.ts', '.tsx', '.js', '.jsx',\n    '.yaml', '.yml', '.json',\n    '.css', '.scss', '.less',\n    '.md', \n    '.sh', '.bash',\n    '.env.example',\n    'Dockerfile',\n    '.dockerignore'\n  ],\n  \n  briefContentTypes: [\n    '.svg', '.png', '.jpg', '.jpeg', '.gif', '.webp', '.ico',\n    '.ttf', '.woff', '.woff2', '.eot', '.otf',\n    '.mp3', '.wav', '.ogg', '.mp4', '.webm',\n    '.pdf', '.doc', '.docx', '.xls', '.xlsx'\n  ],\n  \n  priorityRules: {\n    critical: [\n      /src\\/app\\/\\(main\\)\\/layout\\.tsx$/,\n      /lib\\/security\\.ts$/,\n      /scripts\\/generate-context\\.js$/,\n      /\\.github\\/workflows\\//,\n      /\\.meta\\//,\n      /public\\/manifest\\.json$/,\n      /public\\/icons\\/.*\\.svg$/,\n      /next\\.config\\.js$/,\n      /package\\.json$/,\n      /tsconfig\\.json$/,\n      /.gitignore$/\n    ],\n    high: [\n      /src\\/components\\/ui\\//,\n      /src\\/app\\/api\\//,\n      /lib\\/ai-analysis\\.ts$/,\n      /lib\\/date-utils\\.ts$/,\n      /public\\/locales\\//,\n      /tailwind\\.config\\.js$/,\n      /\\.env\\.example$/,\n      /data\\/people\\//,\n      /data\\/events\\//\n    ],\n    medium: [\n      /src\\/app\\/admin\\//,\n      /src\\/components\\/(timeline|graph)\\//,\n      /lib\\/(backup|telegram)\\.ts$/,\n      /public\\/images\\//,\n      /docs\\//,\n      /\\.prettierrc$/,\n      /\\.eslintrc\\.json$/\n    ]\n  },\n  \n  adaptiveLimits: {\n    maxLines: 10000,\n    criticalPercentage: 60,\n    highPercentage: 20,\n    mediumPercentage: 10,\n    guidelinesPercentage: 10\n  }\n};\n\n// Main generation function\nfunction generateContextFiles() {\n  console.log('üîç Generating context files...');\n  \n  // Create .meta directory if not exists\n  if (!fs.existsSync(META_DIR)) {\n    fs.mkdirSync(META_DIR, { recursive: true });\n  }\n  \n  // Generate full file\n  const fullContent = generateFullFile();\n  fs.writeFileSync(FULL_FILE, fullContent, 'utf8');\n  \n  // Generate adaptive file\n  const adaptiveContent = generateAdaptiveFile();\n  fs.writeFileSync(ADAPTIVE_FILE, adaptiveContent, 'utf8');\n  \n  console.log('‚úÖ Context files generated successfully!');\n  console.log(`   Full file: ${countLines(fullContent)} lines`);\n  console.log(`   Adaptive file: ${countLines(adaptiveContent)} lines`);\n}\n\n// Helper functions for file scanning, content generation, etc.\n\ngenerateContextFiles();\n```\n\n#===============================================================================\n# SECURITY ARCHITECTURE\n#===============================================================================\n\n## SECURITY LAYERS\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    A[User] -->|1. HTTPS| B[Cloudflare]\n    B -->|2. WAF| C[Vercel]\n    C -->|3. Next.js Middleware| D[API Routes]\n    D -->|4. JWT validation| E[Protected Data]\n    E -->|5. Encryption| F[Yandex Cloud]\n    F -->|6. Audit| G[GitHub Actions]\n```\n\n## ADMIN AUTHENTICATION\n- GitHub OAuth with whitelist of admin accounts\n- JWT token validation with expiration (7 days)\n- Rate limiting (100 requests/minute per admin)\n- Session management with HttpOnly cookies\n- Audit logging of all admin actions\n\n## DATA PROTECTION\n- Encryption of sensitive data at rest\n- Automatic sanitization of secrets in logs\n- Regular security audits via GitHub Actions\n- Dependency vulnerability scanning\n- Content Security Policy (CSP) headers\n\n## AUTOMATIC SECURITY AUDIT\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/security-audit.yml\nname: Security Audit\n\non:\n  schedule:\n    - cron: '0 9 * * 1'  # Every Monday at 9:00 UTC\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main]\n\njobs:\n  audit:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - name: Check for secrets in code\n        run: |\n          git log -p | grep -Ei '(\\bpassword\\b|\\bsecret\\b|\\bkey\\b|\\btoken\\b|YANDEX_GPT_IAM_TOKEN)' && exit 1 || true\n          \n          if [ -f .env ] || [ -f .env.local ]; then\n            echo \"::error::.env files found in repository!\"\n            exit 1\n          fi\n      \n      - name: Validate YAML data\n        run: |\n          npm install -g yaml-cli\n          yaml-validate data/**/*.yaml || exit 1\n      \n      - name: Scan for vulnerabilities\n        run: |\n          npm install -g npm\n          npm audit --audit-level=high || true\n```\n\n#===============================================================================\n# DEPLOYMENT AND INFRASTRUCTURE\n#===============================================================================\n\n## HOSTING ARCHITECTURE\n- Vercel for static site hosting and serverless functions\n- Cloudflare for DDoS protection and caching\n- Yandex Cloud for AI services and backup storage\n- GitHub for source control and CI/CD\n\n## CI/CD PIPELINE\n1. Code push to main branch\n2. GitHub Actions runs tests and builds\n3. Vercel automatically deploys to production\n4. GitHub Actions generates context files\n5. Backup to Yandex.Disk executes\n6. Security audit runs weekly\n\n## MONITORING AND ANALYTICS\n- Plausible.io for privacy-focused analytics\n- GitHub Actions logs for build monitoring\n- Telegram notifications for critical events\n- Uptime monitoring via third-party services\n\n#===============================================================================\n# USER INTERFACE DESIGN\n#===============================================================================\n\n## ADAPTIVE LAYOUT\n```tsx\n// components/ui/ResponsiveContainer.tsx\n'use client';\n\nimport { useState, useEffect } from 'react';\n\nexport function ResponsiveContainer({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {\n  const [orientation, setOrientation] = useState<'portrait' | 'landscape'>('portrait');\n  const [containerHeight, setContainerHeight] = useState('100vh');\n  \n  useEffect(() => {\n    const updateLayout = () => {\n      const isLandscape = window.innerWidth > window.innerHeight;\n      setOrientation(isLandscape ? 'landscape' : 'portrait');\n      \n      // Adjust container height based on orientation\n      if (isLandscape) {\n        setContainerHeight('100vh');\n      } else {\n        setContainerHeight('calc(100vh - 60px)'); // Minus header height\n      }\n    };\n    \n    window.addEventListener('resize', updateLayout);\n    updateLayout();\n    \n    return () => window.removeEventListener('resize', updateLayout);\n  }, []);\n  \n  return (\n    <div \n      className={`transition-all duration-300 ${\n        orientation === 'landscape' \n          ? 'flex flex-row h-screen' \n          : 'flex flex-col min-h-screen'\n      }`}\n      style={{ height: containerHeight }}\n    >\n      {children}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n## VECTOR ICON SYSTEM\n```tsx\n// components/ui/VectorIcons.tsx\nimport { IconType } from 'react-icons';\nimport { FaViolin, FaUserGraduate, FaTools, FaHeart, FaUsers } from 'react-icons/fa';\n\nconst ICON_MAP: Record<string, IconType> = {\n  violinist: FaViolin,\n  teacher: FaUserGraduate,\n  luthier: FaTools,\n  relative: FaHeart,\n  concert: FaUsers\n};\n\nexport function VectorIcon({ type, size = 24, className = '' }: { \n  type: keyof typeof ICON_MAP; \n  size?: number; \n  className?: string;\n}) {\n  const Icon = ICON_MAP[type] || FaViolin;\n  return <Icon size={size} className={`text-current ${className}`} />;\n}\n```\n\n## SHAPE COMPONENTS\n```tsx\n// components/ui/ShapeComponents.tsx\nexport function EventShape({ type, size = 40 }: { type: string; size?: number }) {\n  const shapes = {\n    birth: (\n      <circle cx={size/2} cy={size/2} r={size/2 - 2} \n              fill=\"url(#birthGradient)\" stroke=\"#ef4444\" strokeWidth=\"2\" />\n    ),\n    concert: (\n      <polygon points={`${size/2},0 ${size},${size/3} ${size},${size*2/3} ${size/2},${size} 0,${size*2/3} 0,${size/3}`} \n               fill=\"url(#concertGradient)\" stroke=\"#8b5cf6\" strokeWidth=\"2\" />\n    ),\n    meeting: (\n      <rect x=\"2\" y=\"2\" width={size-4} height={size-4} rx=\"8\" \n            fill=\"url(#meetingGradient)\" stroke=\"#16a34a\" strokeWidth=\"2\" />\n    )\n  };\n  \n  return (\n    <svg width={size} height={size} viewBox={`0 0 ${size} ${size}`}>\n      <defs>\n        <linearGradient id=\"birthGradient\" x1=\"0%\" y1=\"0%\" x2=\"100%\" y2=\"100%\">\n          <stop offset=\"0%\" stopColor=\"#fef2f2\" />\n          <stop offset=\"100%\" stopColor=\"#fecaca\" />\n        </linearGradient>\n        {/* Other gradients */}\n      </defs>\n      {shapes[type as keyof typeof shapes] || shapes.birth}\n    </svg>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n#===============================================================================\n# DATA STRUCTURE EXAMPLES\n#===============================================================================\n\n## PERSON DATA STRUCTURE (YAML)\n```yaml\n# data/people/heifetz.yaml\nid: heifetz\nnames:\n  primary: \"Jascha Heifetz\"\n  variants:\n    - \"–Ø—à–∞ –•–µ–π—Ñ–µ—Ü\"\n    - \"Jascha Heifetz\"\n    - \"–•–µ–π—Ñ–µ—Ü –î–∂.\"\nbirth:\n  gregorian: \"1901-02-02\"\n  julian: \"1901-01-20\"\n  display: \"February 2, 1901 (Vilnius, Russian Empire)\"\ndeath:\n  gregorian: \"1987-12-10\"\n  display: \"December 10, 1987 (Los Angeles, California, USA)\"\nbio:\n  short: \"Russian-American violinist, widely regarded as one of the greatest violinists of all time\"\n  full: |\n    Jascha Heifetz was born on February 2, 1901 in Vilnius, Lithuania (then part of the Russian Empire) to Leopold Heifetz, a violinist and teacher. He showed extraordinary musical talent from an early age, beginning violin lessons at age 3 and performing publicly by age 5.\n    \n    In 1906, he entered the Vilnius Music School under Ilya Malats, and in 1907 his family moved to Saint Petersburg where he studied under Leopold Auer at the Saint Petersburg Conservatory. By age 11, he was performing full violin concertos.\n    \n    1917 was a pivotal year - after the October Revolution, Heifetz and his family emigrated to the United States. On November 27, 1917, he made his legendary debut at Carnegie Hall in New York under conductor Walter Damrosch. The concert caused a sensation, with critics calling him \"the greatest violinist in the world.\"\n    \n    Heifetz became an American citizen in 1925. Known for his impeccable technique, pure tone, and unique interpretations, he owned several famous instruments including the \"Dolphin\" Stradivarius (1714), which he acquired in 1951.\n    \n    From 1962 to 1972, Heifetz taught at the University of California, Los Angeles. Among his students were many renowned violinists. In his later years, he focused primarily on teaching and recording.\n    \n    Jascha Heifetz died on December 10, 1987 in Los Angeles from kidney failure. He is buried at Mount Sinai Memorial Park in Los Angeles.\ninstruments:\n  - maker: \"stradivari\"\n    year: \"1714\"\n    nickname: \"Dolphin\"\n    description: \"Famous violin by Antonio Stradivari from 1714, nicknamed 'Dolphin' due to the shape of its body. Heifetz acquired it in 1951 and played it until the end of his career.\"\n    current_location: \"Museo del Violino in Cremona, Italy (after Heifetz's death)\"\nconnections:\n  - type: \"teacher\"\n    target: \"auer\"\n    period: \"1907-1917\"\n    description: \"Main teacher at Saint Petersburg Conservatory. Auer called Heifetz his most talented student.\"\n  - type: \"relative\"\n    target: \"heifetz-father\"\n    relation: \"father\"\n    name: \"Leopold Heifetz\"\n    period: \"1873-1934\"\n    description: \"Violinist and music teacher, Jascha's first teacher\"\n  - type: \"relative\"\n    target: \"heifetz-wife\"\n    relation: \"wife\"\n    name: \"Francesca Heifetz (n√©e Gardeli)\"\n    period: \"1928-1945\"\n    description: \"Marriage lasted 17 years, they had two children: Julian and Vivian\"\n  - type: \"friend\"\n    target: \"rachmaninoff\"\n    period: \"1918-1943\"\n    description: \"Close friendship with Sergei Rachmaninoff, joint concerts and recordings\"\nicon: \"violin\"\n```\n\n## EVENT DATA STRUCTURE (YAML)\n```yaml\n# data/events/carnegie-1917.yaml\nid: carnegie-1917\ntitle:\n  primary: \"Carnegie Hall Debut\"\n  variants:\n    - \"Heifetz New York Concert\"\n    - \"Heifetz Carnegie Hall Debut\"\n    - \"First US Concert\"\n    - \"Historic 1917 Debut\"\ndate:\n  gregorian: \"1917-11-27\"\n  julian: \"1917-11-14\"\n  display: \"November 27, 1917\"\ndescription:\n  short: \"Jascha Heifetz's first concert in the United States, after which critics called him 'the world's greatest violinist'\"\n  full: |\n    The concert took place on November 27, 1917 at Carnegie Hall (New York) under the direction of conductor Walter Damrosch with the New York Symphony Orchestra.\n    \n    The program included:\n    - Violin Concerto by Tchaikovsky in D major, Op. 35\n    - Violin Concerto by Paganini in D major, Op. 61\n    - Nocturne by Grieg (in arrangement)\n    - Sabre Dance from \"Gayaneh\" by Khachaturian (prelude)\n    \n    The concert was sold out. After the first movement, the hall erupted in applause, and after the second - critics declared that \"the musical world had never heard anything like this before.\" The New York Times wrote: \"This 16-year-old boy has rewritten all the rules of violin playing.\"\n    \n    This concert marked the beginning of Heifetz's American career and became a turning point in the history of performance art.\nlocation: \"Carnegie Hall, New York, USA\"\ntype: \"concert\"\nparticipants:\n  - heifetz\n  - damrosch\n  - new-york-symphony\nmedia:\n  - type: \"audio\"\n    url: \"https://archive.org/heifetz-carnegie-1917.mp3\"\n    title: \"Performance fragment\"\n    duration: \"00:03:45\"\n    description: \"Archive recording with noise (digital reconstruction from 1990s)\"\n  - type: \"photo\"\n    url: \"https://archive.org/carnegie-hall-1917-audience.jpg\"\n    title: \"Carnegie Hall audience during concert\"\n    description: \"Black and white photograph taken during intermission\"\nhistorical_significance: |\n  This concert is considered one of the most significant events in 20th century music history. It:\n  1. Introduced American audiences to a new level of performance mastery\n  2. Launched Heifetz's career as an international star\n  3. Changed violin performance standards worldwide\n  4. Became a symbol of cultural exchange between Europe and America during wartime\n```\n\n#===============================================================================\n# SYNCHRONIZATION AND CI/CD\n#===============================================================================\n\n## SYNCHRONIZATION SCRIPTS\n\n### sync.bat (Windows)\n```batch\n@echo off\necho ========================================\necho   SYNCHRONIZATION WITH GITHUB\necho ========================================\necho.\necho 1. Checking repository status...\ngit status --short\n\necho.\necho 2. Adding all changes...\ngit add .\ngit status --short\n\necho.\necho 3. Committing changes (if any)...\ngit commit -m \"chore: auto-commit changes\" --no-verify\n\necho.\necho 4. Getting changes from remote repository...\ngit pull origin main --rebase\n\nif %errorlevel% neq 0 (\n    echo.\n    echo ‚ö†Ô∏è  CONFLICTS DETECTED!\n    echo    Resolve conflicts manually, then execute:\n    echo    git add .\n    echo    git rebase --continue\n    echo    sync.bat\n    pause\n    exit /b 1\n)\n\necho.\necho 5. Pushing local changes...\ngit push origin main\n\nif %errorlevel% neq 0 (\n    echo.\n    echo ‚ö†Ô∏è  PUSH ERROR!\n    echo    Try again after manual resolution.\n    pause\n    exit /b 1\n)\n\necho.\necho ========================================\necho   ‚úÖ SYNCHRONIZATION SUCCESSFUL!\necho ========================================\npause\n```\n\n### full-sync.bat (Windows)\n```batch\n@echo off\necho ========================================\necho   FULL SYNCHRONIZATION\necho   (with context generation)\necho ========================================\necho.\necho 1. Synchronization with GitHub...\ncall sync.bat\n\nif %errorlevel% neq 0 (\n    echo Synchronization error. Aborting.\n    pause\n    exit /b 1\n)\n\necho.\necho 2. Generating context files...\nnpm run generate-context\n\nif %errorlevel% neq 0 (\n    echo Context generation error. Aborting.\n    pause\n    exit /b 1\n)\n\necho.\necho 3. Pushing updated context...\ngit add .meta/\ngit commit -m \"chore: auto-update context files\" --no-verify\ngit push origin main\n\nif %errorlevel% neq 0 (\n    echo Context push error. Aborting.\n    pause\n    exit /b 1\n)\n\necho.\necho ========================================\necho   ‚úÖ FULL SYNCHRONIZATION COMPLETE!\necho ========================================\npause\n```\n\n## GITHUB ACTIONS WORKFLOW\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/auto-sync.yml\nname: Auto Sync and Context Generation\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n    paths-ignore:\n      - '.github/workflows/auto-sync.yml'\n  workflow_dispatch:\n  schedule:\n    - cron: '0 2 * * *'  # Daily at 2:00 UTC\n\njobs:\n  sync:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      contents: write\n\n    steps:\n      - name: Checkout repository\n        uses: actions/checkout@v4\n        with:\n          fetch-depth: 0\n          token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n      \n      - name: Setup Node.js\n        uses: actions/setup-node@v3\n        with:\n          node-version: 18\n          cache: 'npm'\n      \n      - name: Install dependencies\n        run: npm ci\n      \n      - name: Generate context files\n        run: node scripts/generate-context.js\n      \n      - name: Configure Git\n        run: |\n          git config user.name \"github-actions[bot]\"\n          git config user.email \"41898282+github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com\"\n      \n      - name: Commit and push changes\n        run: |\n          git add .meta/\n          git status\n          if ! git diff --cached --quiet; then\n            git commit -m \"chore: auto-update context files\" || echo \"Commit failed but continuing\"\n          fi\n          git push origin HEAD:${{ github.ref_name }} || echo \"Push failed but continuing\"\n```\n\n#===============================================================================\n# GETTING STARTED INSTRUCTIONS\n#===============================================================================\n\n## INITIAL SETUP\n1. Clone repository:\n   ```bash\n   git clone https://github.com/apel-s-in/music-connections.git\n   cd music-connections\n   ```\n\n2. Install dependencies:\n   ```bash\n   npm install\n   ```\n\n3. Create environment file:\n   ```bash\n   cp .env.example .env.local\n   ```\n   Fill in the required secrets from Vercel dashboard\n\n4. Start development server:\n   ```bash\n   npm run dev\n   ```\n\n## ADDING NEW VIOLINISTS\n1. Create YAML file in `data/people/` following the template\n2. Add connections to other people using their IDs\n3. Run synchronization script:\n   ```bash\n   call full-sync.bat\n   ```\n\n## ADMIN ACCESS\n1. Navigate to `/admin` in development mode\n2. Log in with GitHub account (must be in admin whitelist)\n3. Use AI recommendations panel to get suggestions for new content\n4. Edit data directly through the admin interface\n\n## DEPLOYMENT\n1. Push changes to main branch:\n   ```bash\n   git push origin main\n   ```\n2. Vercel will automatically deploy the application\n3. GitHub Actions will generate context files and update backups\n\n## TROUBLESHOOTING\n- **Context files not generating**: Check GitHub Actions logs for errors\n- **Deployment failures**: Check Vercel dashboard for build logs\n- **Missing data**: Ensure YAML files are properly formatted and added to git\n- **Synchronization conflicts**: Use `git rebase` to resolve merge conflicts\n\n#===============================================================================\n# FUTURE ENHANCEMENTS\n#===============================================================================\n\n## PLANNED FEATURES\n- Multi-language support (English, Russian, German)\n- Mobile app version with offline access\n- Audio playback of historical recordings\n- Interactive quizzes and educational content\n- 3D visualization of instrument construction\n- Collaborative editing mode for researchers\n- Integration with MusicBrainz and Wikidata APIs\n\n## PERFORMANCE OPTIMIZATIONS\n- Lazy loading of timeline data\n- Virtualized rendering for large graphs\n- Client-side caching strategies\n- Progressive image loading\n- Code splitting for faster initial load\n\n## ACCESSIBILITY IMPROVEMENTS\n- Full screen reader support\n- Keyboard navigation enhancements\n- High contrast mode\n- Text size adjustment\n- Reduced motion options\n\n#===============================================================================\n# CONTACT AND SUPPORT\n#===============================================================================\n\n## DEVELOPER CONTACT\n- GitHub Issues: https://github.com/apel-s-in/music-connections/issues\n- Telegram: @developer_username\n\n## USER SUPPORT\n- Feedback form in application\n- Email: support@music-connections.app\n- Community forum (planned)\n\n## CONTRIBUTING\n- Pull requests welcome for bug fixes and documentation\n- Feature requests should be discussed in Issues first\n- Follow code style guidelines and include tests\n- All contributions must comply with MIT license\n\n#===============================================================================\n# LICENSE AND CREDITS\n#===============================================================================\n\n## LICENSE\nMIT License\n\nCopyright (c) 2024 Music Connections Project\n\nPermission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy\nof this software and associated documentation files (the \"Software\"), to deal\nin the Software without restriction, including without limitation the rights\nto use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell\ncopies of the Software, and to permit persons to whom the Software is\nfurnished to do so, subject to the following conditions:\n\nThe above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all\ncopies or substantial portions of the Software.\n\nTHE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED \"AS IS\", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR\nIMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,\nFITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE\nAUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER\nLIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM,\nOUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE\nSOFTWARE.\n\n## ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS\n- Yandex Cloud for AI services\n- GitHub for hosting and CI/CD infrastructure\n- Vercel for deployment platform\n- Open source community for libraries and tools\n- Historical music scholars for data verification\n\n#===============================================================================\n# VERSION HISTORY\n#===============================================================================\n\n## VERSION 3.0 (CURRENT)\n- Complete context generation system\n- Yandex GPT integration for recommendations\n- Telegram feedback system\n- PDF export functionality\n- Yandex.Donate integration\n- Backup to Yandex.Disk\n- Automatic synchronization scripts\n- Vector graphics system\n- Responsive layout for all devices\n\n## VERSION 2.0\n- Admin panel with authentication\n- Connection graph visualization\n- Timeline component with zoom\n- Data structure and automation scripts\n- Initial security implementation\n- GitHub Actions CI/CD pipeline\n\n## VERSION 1.0\n- Basic project setup\n- Initial data structure\n- Core visualization components\n- Deployment infrastructure\n\n#===============================================================================\n# END OF TECHNICAL SPECIFICATION\n#===============================================================================\n\nThis document contains the complete technical specification for the Music Connections PWA project. It is automatically generated and updated through the context ge